The paper discusses the large-scale analysis of scholarly artifact usage, which falls under the domain of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The ontology presented in the paper is specifically designed for modeling scholarly artifacts, which could also fall under the categories of cyberinfrastructure (cs.CY) and social networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a semantic network model, which could involve database systems (cs.DB).
